  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Personal Driver (Evening)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Your Role</strong></p><ul><li><p>Provide safe, smooth, punctual, and discreet chauffeuring services for the Group CEO and family members.</p></li><li><p>Maintain the assigned vehicle in immaculate condition at all times (interior and exterior).</p></li><li><p>Conduct routine vehicle inspections and ensure the car is always roadworthy and presentable.</p></li><li><p>Promptly report and arrange rectification for any dents, scratches, or mechanical issues.</p></li><li><p>Plan optimal routes and adjust in real time to ensure punctuality and a comfortable ride experience.</p></li><li><p>Observe and comply strictly with all Singapore traffic laws and company driving policies.</p></li><li><p>Exercise the highest level of care and professionalism when ferrying, parking, and maneuvering vehicles.</p></li><li><p>Maintain strict confidentiality, discretion, and professionalism at all times.</p></li><li><p>Provide courteous, respectful, and service-oriented support to the CEO and family.</p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></p><ul><li><p>Valid Singapore <strong>Class 3 driving license</strong> with a clean driving record.</p></li><li><p><strong>Minimum 1 years’ experience</strong> as a personal, executive, or VIP driver.</p></li><li><p>Strong driving competency with excellent defensive driving and road safety awareness.</p></li><li><p>Familiar with Singapore roads, traffic patterns, and navigation systems.</p></li><li><p>Mature, calm, cautious, and highly responsible.</p></li><li><p>Well-groomed and punctual, with a professional and service-oriented demeanor.</p></li><li><p>High integrity, discretion, and respect for confidentiality.</p></li></ul><p><br />\n\n</p>",
